  "tutorial.try_it": "Try it",

  "tutorial.mock_guide": "<h4>How to Use Mock Server</h4><ol><li>Enter the <code>Method</code> (GET/POST etc.) and <code>Path</code> in the left form.</li><li>Write the JSON to return in <code>Response Body</code> and click <code>Save</code>.</li><li>Check the endpoint in the saved Mock list and send actual HTTP requests to test.</li><li>View traffic details in the <code>Request/Response Log</code> section below.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Leave the request body empty to match any incoming request.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.charcount_guide": "<h4>How to Use Character Count</h4><ol><li>Paste the text you want to check into the input area.</li><li>Character count, byte count, and word count are automatically shown per line.</li><li>Click column headers to sort by that metric.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Paste multiple lines at once for easy line-by-line comparison.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.mybatis_guide": "<h4>How to Use MyBatis Log Converter</h4><ol><li>Paste the MyBatis log output (Preparing + Parameters) as-is.</li><li>SQL and parameters are auto-separated, and values are bound to <code>?</code> placeholders.</li><li>Toggle <code>Remove comments</code> and <code>Format</code> options as needed.</li><li>Copy the result and execute it directly in your DB client.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Paste the full Preparing/Parameters log and it will be auto-split.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.jsonformat_guide": "<h4>How to Use JSON Format</h4><ol><li>Paste JSON into the editor and it will be auto-formatted.</li><li>Use <code>Sort</code> to alphabetize keys and <code>Minify</code> to compress to one line.</li><li>Explore the structure with <code>Tree Viewer</code> and save to DB with <code>Temp Save</code>.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Use <code>Remove Empty</code> to clean up null values, empty strings, and empty arrays at once.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.translate_guide": "<h4>How to Use Translate</h4><ol><li>Select the <code>Source language</code> at the top.</li><li>Check the <code>Target languages</code> using checkboxes (multiple selection allowed).</li><li>Enter your text and click the <code>Translate</code> button.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> You must set OPENAI_API_KEY in the .env file to use this feature.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.csv_guide": "<h4>How to Use CSV Editor</h4><ol><li>Drag and drop a CSV file or paste with <code>Ctrl+V</code>.</li><li>Click cells directly in the grid to edit. You can add or delete rows and columns.</li><li>Change the output encoding from the <code>Encoding</code> dropdown and download.</li><li>Use <code>Duplicate Analysis</code> to find duplicate data in a specific column.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Click column headers to access sorting and filtering features.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.markdown_guide": "<h4>How to Use Markdown Editor</h4><ol><li>Write Markdown in the left editor and see live preview on the right.</li><li>Use the toolbar for <code>Bold</code>, <code>Link</code>, <code>Table</code>, etc. or use keyboard shortcuts.</li><li>Use <code>Save</code> to store in DB and <code>History</code> for version management.</li><li>Use <code>AI Review</code> to auto-correct spelling and style.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Use Ctrl+B (bold), Ctrl+I (italic) and other shortcuts for quick formatting.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.paramchanger_guide": "<h4>How to Use Parameter Converter</h4><ol><li>Paste a list of values into the left input area (separated by spaces, newlines, commas, etc.).</li><li>The delimiter is auto-detected, but you can change it manually.</li><li>Select your desired <code>Output format</code> (comma, quoted, SQL IN, etc.) on the right for instant conversion.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Convert to SQL IN format to get ready-to-use WHERE id IN ('A','B','C') queries.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.pdfconvert_guide": "<h4>How to Use PDF Converter</h4><ol><li>Drag and drop files or click to upload.</li><li>Set options like paper size, orientation, and margins.</li><li>Click <code>Convert to PDF</code> for individual files or <code>Merge into one PDF</code> to combine.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Markdown files can be loaded directly from saved items.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.diffcompare_guide": "<h4>How to Use Diff Compare</h4><ol><li>Select comparison mode from the top tabs: <code>Text</code>, <code>File</code>, or <code>Folder</code>.</li><li>Paste content into both sides and click <code>Compare</code>.</li><li>Click a change block to select it, then use <code>Alt+Left/Right</code> to apply to one side.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Use Alt+Up/Down to quickly navigate between change blocks.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.git_guide": "<h4>How to Use Git Manager</h4><ol><li>Enter a repository path or use <code>Select Folder</code> to choose a Git repository.</li><li>Check the files to commit from the changed files list and enter a message.</li><li>Click <code>Commit</code> to commit. You can also switch branches or create new ones.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> Register commit message templates to auto-replace variables like {branch} and {date}.</p></div>",
  "tutorial.dataai_guide": "<h4>How to Use Data AI</h4><ol><li>Describe the data you want in natural language (e.g. 'User list 50 rows with name/email/age').</li><li>Set the <code>Output format</code> (CSV, JSON, TSV) and <code>Count</code>.</li><li>Click <code>Generate</code> and AI will create the data for you.</li><li>Send results to CSV Editor or JSON Format, or save to DB.</li></ol><div class='md-alert md-alert-tip'><p class='md-alert-title'>💡 Tip</p><p> The more specific your description (column names, value ranges, etc.), the more accurate the data.</p></div>"
}
